:: head_ms_head_mm_3
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>You will not lose anything, Caelan. This is not a reversal. It is a rebalancing. A different truth carved from the same stone.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>Ugh. That‚Äôs‚Ä¶ stronger than I remember.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>It has to be. Your body had accepted softness. Now it must be reminded of edge.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>My jaw‚Ä¶ it‚Äôs tightening. Gods, it‚Äôs like sinew pulling back into place.<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|head_ms_head_mm_4]]
<</nobr>>

:: head_ms_head_mm_4
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>Your brow is knitting deeper. There‚Äôs more shadow to your gaze already.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>It hurts. Not the potion. Just‚Ä¶ seeing it return. This isn‚Äôt just my face. It‚Äôs him. The version of me who never questioned anything.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>Does he scare you?<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>He disappoints me. But I don‚Äôt hate him.<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|head_ms_head_mm_5]]
<</nobr>>

:: head_ms_head_mm_5
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>Then you carry him forward with wisdom, not regret.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>There‚Äôs strength here. But less peace.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>Strength can be a mask or a mirror. You decide which.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>I‚Äôll need both, won‚Äôt I?<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|head_ms_head_mm_6]]

