:: head_ms_head_fs_1
<<nobr>>
<<speech "thalara">>Today‚Äôs potion carries a softer magic, but make no mistake its effects are no less profound. It touches your reflection first, and then‚Ä¶ the soul behind it.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>I thought I‚Äôd gotten used to these sessions. But this one feels‚Ä¶ closer. Like it‚Äôll change what people see in my eyes.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>Because it will. Until now, your features still echoed both the prince and the path before you. But after this‚Ä¶ the ambiguity fades.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>So I stop being a ‚Äòhe who looks softer‚Äô and become something‚Ä¶ uncertain?<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|head_ms_head_fs_2]]
<</nobr>>

:: head_ms_head_fs_2
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>No, Caelan. You begin to become a ‚Äòshe who has not yet arrived.‚Äô There is a difference.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>I keep expecting to wake up and see my old face again. Jawline sharp. Eyes like my father‚Äôs. But every time, I drift further. Like memory turning to fog.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>Not fog. Mist. And mist can reveal as much as it hides.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>Will it hurt?<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|head_ms_head_fs_3]]
<</nobr>>

:: head_ms_head_fs_3
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>Not in the way you fear. There may be warmth tingling along the cheekbones, a tightness in your lips. But the real ache comes when you look at the mirror‚Ä¶ and she looks back.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>Still bitter as ever‚Ä¶<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>The bitterness is not from the potion. It‚Äôs from what it asks of you.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>My skin feels‚Ä¶ thinner. Not weaker. Just‚Ä¶ like silk instead of leather.<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|head_ms_head_fs_4]]
<</nobr>>

:: head_ms_head_fs_4
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>The cheekbones will lift now. Your lips will taper. The muscles behind your eyes will relax, letting softness pool there.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>How do you know all this? Every inch of change, every flicker?<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>I‚Äôve walked others through this mist, Caelan. Queens who were not born as women. Nobles who gave up comfort for clarity. Some of them screamed. Others‚Ä¶ sang.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>And what did I do?<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|head_ms_head_fs_5]]
<</nobr>>

:: head_ms_head_fs_5
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>You watched the mirror. And you listened. That is rarer than you think.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>She‚Äôs already there, isn‚Äôt she? The version of me I haven‚Äôt met yet.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>She‚Äôs not a stranger, Caelan. She‚Äôs you without your armor.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>That‚Äôs the part I don‚Äôt know how to face. What if I like her? What if I don‚Äôt?<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|head_ms_head_fs_6]]
<</nobr>>

:: head_ms_head_fs_6
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>You don‚Äôt need to love her yet. Just let her breathe.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>My lips‚Ä¶ they‚Äôre thinner. Softer. Eyes look‚Ä¶ different.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>You‚Äôre not supposed to recognize her completely. Not yet. She‚Äôll grow clearer with each choice you make.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>I feel like I‚Äôm standing between two portraits. Neither finished.<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|head_ms_head_fs_7]]
<</nobr>>


:: head_ms_head_fs_7
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>Then let your reflection be a painting in progress. And remember what you become doesn‚Äôt erase who you were.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>Into the mirror‚Äôs mist‚Ä¶ and through it, I suppose.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>Exactly, my lady. And mist always clears‚Ä¶ when it‚Äôs time.<</speech>><br>
