<<speech "mc">>What if I liked the way she smiled? It was different. Lighter. As if the world wasn‚Äôt watching so closely.<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|head_fs_head_ms_2]]
<</nobr>>

:: head_fs_head_ms_2
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>Then remember it. Even as your lips shift, remember how that smile felt. No transformation can take your truth from you.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>Still bitter. But not like the last ones. This one tastes‚Ä¶ dry. Empty, almost.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>Because it‚Äôs not building something new it‚Äôs closing a chapter. There‚Äôs melancholy in that. Even in power regained.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>My skin‚Ä¶ feels thicker again. Less delicate. Jaw feels‚Ä¶ heavier?<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|head_fs_head_ms_3]]
<</nobr>>

:: head_fs_head_ms_3
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>The lines return gradually. The cheeks broaden. The balance of muscle in your face begins to reassert.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>So I‚Äôm becoming him again. Not her. Not both. Just‚Ä¶ him.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>No, Caelan. You are still you. But the world will see him first again. It‚Äôs only a mask if you forget who's wearing it.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>Why does it hurt more going back than it did going forward?<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|head_fs_head_ms_4]]
<</nobr>>


:: head_fs_head_ms_4
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>Because forward was the unknown. Backward carries memory. The weight of what you‚Äôve felt, lived, questioned. That‚Äôs heavier than transformation.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>I can already feel my cheekbones dulling‚Ä¶ my lips firming. The softness is still there, but it's‚Ä¶ covered. Hidden.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>And that‚Äôs a kind of strength too. You‚Äôve touched grace. Now you carry it inside, even if the mirror forgets.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>What will people see now?<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|head_fs_head_ms_5]]
<</nobr>>

:: head_fs_head_ms_5
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>They‚Äôll see a prince who once glimpsed the queen within. That vision doesn‚Äôt vanish. It lives in your voice, your eyes, your choices.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>Will she miss me? The one in the mist?<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>She won‚Äôt need to. She is you. She‚Äôs waiting, not mourning.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>I didn‚Äôt expect to grieve.<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|head_fs_head_ms_6]]
<</nobr>>

:: head_fs_head_ms_6
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>Transformation always leaves echoes. Some fade. Some follow. But all of them shape the ruler you will be.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>Then let her echo guide me. Even if the world calls me prince again‚Ä¶ she was real. She is real.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>And should the time come to find her again‚Ä¶ the mist will part. As it always does.<</speech>><br>
