[[Move Forth|head_fs_head_fm_3]]
<</nobr>>

:: head_fs_head_fm_3
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>Yes. Or conquers one, without ever raising a voice.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>Tingles this time. Right behind the eyes... and along my jaw. It‚Äôs strange.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>The potion eases the underlying muscles. Shapes them to respond to subtler emotion smiles, glances, soft amusement. It draws out grace you didn‚Äôt know you possessed.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>My chin looks... different. Pointed?<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|head_fs_head_fm_4]]
<</nobr>>

:: head_fs_head_fm_4
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>Tapered, yes. And your lips are beginning to round. Soon, every expression you make will be read differently. Felt differently.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>That sounds... dangerous.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>It is. But so is any form of power. Your face will no longer command it will compel.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>Would people even believe I was ever a prince?<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|head_fs_head_fm_5]]
<</nobr>>

:: head_fs_head_fm_5
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>Some may forget. Others will only whisper. And a few will remember and revere you for the journey.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>There‚Äôs something unreal about it all. Like watching someone else emerge from inside me.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>Not someone else. Just another truth. A truth you buried beneath duty, sword drills, and expectation.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>And if I wanted to stop here?<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|head_fs_head_fm_6]]
<</nobr>>

:: head_fs_head_fm_6
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>You could. But you'd carry an unfinished song in your skin. And songs half-sung tend to haunt their singers.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>It already doesn‚Äôt feel like mine. And yet... it‚Äôs not wrong.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>That‚Äôs because you‚Äôre not losing yourself you‚Äôre unfolding. And every fold you reveal adds depth to the queen you may yet become.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>I don‚Äôt know if I‚Äôll ever believe that fully.<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|head_fs_head_fm_7]]
<</nobr>>


:: head_fs_head_fm_7
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>Then believe in the possibility. In the silence of a hall when you walk in. In the way a rival stumbles over their words beneath your gaze. That is real. That is yours.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>So‚Ä¶ after this, I won‚Äôt just look like someone new. I‚Äôll feel it, too?<</speech>><br>

<<speech "thalara">>You‚Äôll begin to. And the world will respond. Be ready, Caelan. Beauty carries its own burden.<</speech>><br>

<<speech "mc">>Then teach me to wield it. Not like a mask‚Ä¶ but like a blade.<</speech>><br>

[[Move Forth|head_fs_head_fm_8]]
<</nobr>>

:: head_fs_head_fm_8
<<nobr>>

<<speech "thalara">>Spoken like a true ruler. Grace sharpened is grace that conquers.<</speech>><br>
